<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-03-11T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-03-11T18:00:00-05:00" n="566" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d566">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72115/3271</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in China</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_RPS1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Reinsch</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-03-11T18:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">March 11, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Your February 20, 4 p.m. Department today informing British
                                Ambassador, Washington, that Government of the United States is
                                willing to incur its share of expenses of deportation and internment
                                of enemy alien subjects from China.<note n="1" xml:id="d566fn1">The
                                    memorandum conveying this information, prepared as an answer to
                                    the British Embassy’s memorandum of Feb. 23, <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_634">p. 634</ref>, bears
                                    annotations showing that it was not sent (File No.
                                    763.72115/3277).</note>
                            </p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_PFL1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>